theorem
Th51: (for A being (Matrix of n,K) holds (for j0 being (Element of ( NAT )) holds ((1 <= j0 & j0 <= n) implies ((for i holds ((1 <= i & i <= n) implies (( ( A * ( SwapDiagonal (K,n,j0) ) ) * (i,j0) ) = ( A * (i,1) ) & ( ( A * ( SwapDiagonal (K,n,j0) ) ) * (i,1) ) = ( A * (i,j0) )))) & (for i holds (for j holds ((((((j <> 1 & j <> j0) & 1 <= i) & i <= n) & 1 <= j) & j <= n) implies ( ( A * ( SwapDiagonal (K,n,j0) ) ) * (i,j) ) = ( A * (i,j) ))))))))
proof
let A being (Matrix of n,K);
let j0 being (Element of ( NAT ));
assume A1: (1 <= j0 & j0 <= n);
A2: ( ( ( SwapDiagonal (K,n,j0) ) * ( A @ ) ) @ ) = ( ( ( A @ ) @ ) * ( ( SwapDiagonal (K,n,j0) ) @ ) ) by CKB36:1
.= ( A * ( ( SwapDiagonal (K,n,j0) ) @ ) ) by MATRIXR2:29
